      <h2>Choosing Based on Your Trade</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Ironworkers & Structural Steel:</strong> 3M DBI-Sala ExoFit X200 (4.7★) for positioning capability and all-day comfort, or the Full Body Harness with Internal Lanyard (4.5★) for snag-free work around rebar.</li>
        <li><strong>Roofers:</strong> TRSMIMA Roofing Harness Kit (4.5★) or the TRSMIMA Kit (B0CRHKFYX5, 4.5★) with forward D-ring placement for better mobility on slopes.</li>
        <li><strong>Scaffolders:</strong> 3M Protecta P200 (4.8★) for rugged, no-fuss reliability and pass-through buckles that stay put.</li>
        <li><strong>General Construction:</strong> Fall Protection Premium Harness (4.6★) or any TRSMIMA kit for value-conscious crew outfitting.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Final Verdict</h2>
      <p>If budget allows, the <strong>3M DBI-Sala ExoFit X200</strong> (4.7★) is the best overall safety harness for construction professionals — it combines premium comfort, versatile D-ring placement, and proven 3M engineering. The <strong>3M Protecta P200</strong> (4.8★) is the highest-rated harness across all price points and is ideal for crews that need a straightforward, tough harness. For value, the <strong>TRSMIMA kits</strong> (4.5★) deliver ANSI-compliant fall protection at a fraction of the cost of premium brands.</p>
      <p>Remember: the best harness is the one your crew will actually wear consistently. Comfort and fit are safety features, not luxuries.</p>

